ad suffered extensive fire damage. The hall was built in 1903 and was originally used as a [[Methodism|Methodist]] mission. The redevelopment was being funded through a public private sector funding agreement, as well as the [[The Prince's Regeneration Trust|Prince's Regeneration Trust]]. Work was finally completed in 2008, some months after the original projected finish date was set.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://princes-regeneration.org/projects/eastbrook-hall-bradford |title=Eastbrook Hall, Bradford |publisher=The Prince's Regeneration Trust |accessdate=2 February 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== The Gatehaus ===\n\n[[The Gatehaus]] is an 11-storey glass building constructed within the Little Germany district. Construction began in 2005 and was completed in 2007 with a total cost of \u00a322&nbsp;million. The project was originally proposed as a 17-storey landmark but was changed due to a rethink after suggestions that its height was incompatible with the surrounding Victorian buildings. The scheme was developed by Asquith Properties.\n\n== See also ==\n{{Commons cat}}\n* [[Forster Square, Bradford]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Bradford}} \n\n[[Category:Areas of Bradford]]\n[[Category:German communities]]\n[[Category:German diaspora in Europe]]\n[[Category:Historic Jewish communities]]\n[[Category:Jewish English history]]\n[[Category:Commercial buildings in England]]\n[[Category:Neoclassical architecture in Yorkshire]]\n", "name_user": "Thoughtfortheday", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eHistory and information:typo", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Little_Germany,_Bradford"}
